      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 48,
      "message": "@Gerard Nope, it's already covered implicitly via the try-catch block in our method:\n\n\ncatch (final Exception e) {\n   log.warn(\"Startup delay unable to apply delay. Proceeding without delay. {}\", e.getMessage());\n}\n\nBut to be more specific and clearer, we can catch UnknownHostException explicitly, log it separately, and fall back if needed. what do you think?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7957,
        "name": "Sourabh Sourabh",
        "display_name": null,
